pr_body:
Add a css class to distinguish between input fields for ltr and rtl languages, so that the text direction can be changed for all input fields that need to be bi-directional using a css rule:
```css
.mt-bidi {
    direction: rtl;
}
```

Fix #56 
@Razzeee This contain some code similar to PR [51](https://github.com/xbmc/addon-check/pull/51).

Should I make this also usable via `.tests-config.json` ?

//CC: @rayluo 
My Change #138 was not right by searching the cache before the token request because at that time we don't know the userID, so the entry returned will not be right.
The right thing to do is to add the token to the cache after the request,  which would override the existing token with newer one, and that is what [device code flow does](https://github.com/AzureAD/azure-activedirectory-library-for-python/blob/dev/adal/token_request.py#L403-L404) for the same reason that the userId is not known yet till you get the token.

One of the main uses of the config_updated signal is to act accordingly to field changes. Signal is already providing the key and the new value, but it misses the old value so anyone can compare if it was changed.

I'm proposing here to send into the signal the old value as well as the new value, so it allows to compare if the value was changed and act accordingly.

@jezdez Could you please take a look and let me know what you think?

